# filter out low abundance data
Kphyseq.tax.level <- phyloseq_filter_prevalence(Kphyseq.tax.level, prev.trh = 0.05, abund.trh = 100, threshold_condition = "AND", abund.type = "total")  

#prev.trh   = Prevalence threshold (default, 0.05 = 5% of samples)
#abund.trh = Abundance threshold (default, NULL). Abundance threshold defines if the OTU should be preserved if its abundance is larger than threshold (e.g., >= 50 reads)
#threshold_condition    = Indicates whether OTU should be kept if it occurs in many samples AND/OR it has high abundance - type of prevalence and abundance conditions, can be "OR" (default) or "AND"
#abund.type= Character string indicating which type of OTU abundance to take into account for filtering ("total", "mean", or "median")

otu_data <- as.matrix(Kphyseq.tax.level@otu_table@.Data)
otu_data <- t(otu_data)
otu_data <- as.data.frame(otu_data)

meta_data <- as.matrix(Kphyseq.tax.level@sam_data)
meta_data <- as.data.frame(meta_data)

###############################################################
## Setting up colour palette
qual_col_pals <- brewer.pal.info[brewer.pal.info$category == 'qual',]   ##  Set up colour libary
col_vector <- unlist(mapply(brewer.pal, qual_col_pals$maxcolors, rownames(qual_col_pals)))
group_colours <- sample(col_vector, length(levels(as.factor(meta_data$Treatment))))
cols <- group_colours[as.factor(meta_data$Treatment)]

## PCoA
dist = phyloseq::distance(Kphyseq.tax.level, method="bray")
ordination = ordinate(Kphyseq, method="PCoA", distance=dist)
plot_ordination(Kphyseq, ordination, color="sample_type") + 
  theme_classic() +
  theme(strip.background = element_blank())

## PCoA suing base R - cmdscale = Classical multidimensional scaling (MDS) of a data matrix. Also known as principal coordinates analysis (Gower, 1966). PCoA focuses on distances, and it tries to extract the dimensions that account for the maximum distances.

###Run for sample type and kdiet
##### code found from = https://f1000research.com/articles/5-1492/v1 

top2 <- names(sort(taxa_sums(Kphyseq_norm_phylum), decreasing = TRUE))[1:N2]
Kphyseq_norm_phylum_top <- prune_taxa(top2, Kphyseq_norm_phylum)

plot_abundance = function(Kphyseq_norm_phylum_top, ylabn = "",
                          Facet = "Phylum",
                          Color = "Phylum"){
  mKphyseq = psmelt(Kphyseq_norm_phylum_top)
  mKphyseq <- subset(mKphyseq, Abundance > 0)
  ggplot(data = mKphyseq,
         mapping = aes_string(x = "sample_type", y = "Abundance",
                              color = Color, fill = Color)) +
    geom_violin(fill = NA) +
    geom_point(size = 1, alpha = 0.3,
               position = position_jitter(width = 0.3)) +
    facet_wrap(facets = Facet) + ylab(ylabn) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
    scale_y_log10()
}

KphyseqRA = transform_sample_counts(Kphyseq_norm_phylum_top, function(x){x / sum(x)})
